snippet.textDisplay: I just want to say, I’m really glad that your deciding to do a water birth for your last baby and especially during this crisis. I agree with wanting to have your family and kids around you for this last pregnancy and special moment. I’m 23 and I have a baby boy that is 15 months now and I’m happy to say that I had a home/water birth and I would do it all over again. I was in labor for a total of 19hrs which was a little painful but it was a beautiful and special moment for us. I had 2 midwives which were the best ever, I would recommend them but we live in TX. I would just recommend doing the hypnobirthing classes which will help you and Austin throughout your labor. Also speak with a couple midwives or if someone recommends you to a midwife that will make you feel and give their all to you and the baby’s Health❤️ I feel like you will do great if you go in with a positive mind and good energy which you always have❣️ I hope you go through with it and I wish the best for you, your family and this pregnancy 💕
